      "grammar": {
        "title": "A1 Grammar Focus: Numbers & Question Formation",
        "sections": [
          {
            "heading": "1. Numbers 0-20",
            "content": "Learn the basic numbers:\n- 0: null, 1: eins, 2: zwei, 3: drei, 4: vier, 5: fünf\n- 6: sechs, 7: sieben, 8: acht, 9: neun, 10: zehn\n- 11: elf, 12: zwölf, 13: dreizehn, 14: vierzehn, 15: fünfzehn\n- 16: sechzehn, 17: siebzehn, 18: achtzehn, 19: neunzehn, 20: zwanzig"
          },
          {
            "heading": "2. Numbers 20-100",
            "content": "German numbers follow a pattern:\n- 20: zwanzig, 30: dreißig, 40: vierzig, 50: fünfzig\n- For numbers like 21-29: say the unit FIRST, then 'und', then the ten\n  → 21: einundzwanzig, 24: vierundzwanzig, 35: fünfunddreißig\n- 100: hundert"
          },
          {
            "heading": "3. Asking Questions: W-Words",
            "content": "German question words always start with 'W':\n- **Wie?** = How? / Wie viel? = How much?\n- **Was?** = What?\n- **Wo?** = Where? / Woher? = Where from? / Wohin? = Where to?\n- **Wer?** = Who?\n- **Wann?** = When?\n- **Warum?** = Why?\n- **Welche?** = Which?"
          },
          {
            "heading": "4. Verb Position in Questions",
            "content": "In questions, the conjugated verb comes FIRST:\n- Statement: Du **kommst** aus Berlin. (You come from Berlin.)\n- Question: **Kommst** du aus Berlin? (Do you come from Berlin?)\n- Statement: Das **kostet** zehn Euro.\n- Question: **Wie viel kostet** das?"
          },
          {
            "heading": "5. Prices & Currency",
            "content": "- Use 'kosten' (to cost) for prices: Das **kostet** fünf Euro.\n- Currency: Euro (no plural 's'), Cent\n- Format: 15,50 € = fünfzehn Euro fünfzig\n- Question: **Wie viel kostet** das? / **Was kostet** das?"
          },
          {
            "heading": "6. Phone Numbers in German",
            "content": "- Say numbers individually or in pairs\n- 'null' for zero\n- Example: 030 48 29 36 → 'null drei null, achtundvierzig, neunundzwanzig, sechsunddreißig'\n- Question: **Wie ist** Ihre Telefonnummer? / **Was ist** Ihre Nummer?"
          },
          {
            "heading": "7. Polite Requests",
            "content": "- **Kann** ich...? = Can I...?\n- **Können** Sie...? = Can you...? (formal)\n- Add 'bitte' for politeness: **Können** Sie das **bitte wiederholen**?\n- 'noch einmal' = one more time, 'langsam' = slowly"
          }
        ]
      },

